Package client.commands

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientCgetgHandler
    Reads the answer from the Server after sending the cgetg request.
    ClientCgetuHandler
    The answer to the client's cgetu request where the server informs this Client about the currently logged in Users.
    ClientChatmHandler
    Parses the command and displays the newly received Message on the Chat Window.
    ClientCpingHandler
    Handles the cping by sending cpong back.
    ClientCpongSender
    Class sends pong to server, if server does not respond before timeout the Client closes socket and shuts down.
    ClientCquitHandler
    Handles the cquit command from the server telling this client that the client specified in the argument has logged off.
    ClientJoingHandler
    Adds the joined user to the game on the client side when the server informs this Client about the newly joined user.
    ClientLeavgHandler
    Removes the user from the game on the Client side (opposite of ClientJoingHandler).
    ClientNewgmHandler
    This command is received when a client has opened a new game.
    ClientNuserHandler
    Handles the nuser command by adding the new user to the userlist IF this user is already logged in.
    ClientReadyHandler
    Informs the ClientGameStartController from the given game about the given user which has chosen their team.
    ClientRmgamHandler
    Removes the game (because every user has left it).
    ClientUnameHandler
    Reads in the answer from the server about the proposed username and (if +OK) loggs the Client in or (if -ERR) proposes the suggested username from the Server.
    CommandHandler
    This is the base class for classes which handle the command and the answer for a specific command Created by flavia on 26.03.17.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Answer
    Works like Command, but with the answers.
    Command
    The different command keywords.
